# Data Center AI — Data Flow (Sensor to UI)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant S as Simulator (simulator.py)
    participant EB as EventBus (event_bus.py)
    participant PC as PersistenceConsumer
    participant DB as SQLite
    participant ML as MLConsumer
    participant SR as RiskScorer
    participant AC as AlertConsumer
    participant WS as WebSocket
    participant UI as React Frontend

    Note over S, EB: STEP 1 — Sensor Data Generation

    S->>S: _synthetic_reading(device)
    Note right of S: Generates temp, power, airflow,<br/>CPU util, humidity, PUE every 2s<br/>(or replays Kaggle CSV if available)

    S->>EB: SensorEvent(device_id, reading)
    par Parallel fan-out
        EB->>PC: on_sensor_event(event)
        EB->>WS: broadcast event
    end

    Note over PC, DB: STEP 2 — Persistence

    PC->>DB: SensorReading INSERT
    Note right of DB: Stored with device_id,<br/>timestamp, all 9 sensor fields

    Note over ML, SR: STEP 3 — ML Inference (every 30s scheduler)

    ML->>DB: Load latest readings for all devices
    ML->>SR: score(anomaly_scores, temps, forecast_upper, ...)
    SR-->>ML: [{risk_score, risk_label, contributing_factors}, ...]
    ML->>ML: update Device.current_risk_score in DB
    ML->>EB: DeviceRiskEvent per device

    Note over EB, AC: STEP 4 — Alert Generation

    alt risk_label = at_risk or critical
        EB->>AC: on_device_risk(event)
        AC->>DB: INSERT AnomalyAlert (or UPDATE if exists)
        AC->>EB: AlertTriggeredEvent
        EB->>WS: broadcast alert
    end

    Note over WS, UI: STEP 5 — Real-time UI Update

    WS->>UI: WebSocket message (sensor_update or alert_triggered)
    UI->>UI: useSensorStore.updateReading()<br/>or useAlertStore.addAlert()
    UI->>UI: React re-renders topology, KPI strip

    Note over UI: STEP 6 — Operator Action (Human-in-the-Loop)

    UI->>API: POST /alerts/{id}/accept
    API->>DB: UPDATE alert status<br/>INSERT WorkOrder
    API->>DB: INSERT AuditLog
    API-->>UI: { work_order, alert }
    UI->>UI: toast.success("Work order created!")
```
